--- C1: x64 RIP-relative BCJ filter (committed d70bfdd, 2026-04-20) ---
Was already implemented in working tree. Verified, committed, updated docs.
Gains vs 2026-04-13 baseline:
  ntdll.dll:    0.4418 -> 0.4348  (-0.70 pts)
  kernel32.dll: 0.4409 -> 0.4375  (-0.34 pts)
  user32.dll:   0.3637 -> 0.3579  (-0.58 pts)
Now beats zstd-9 on all files and bzip2-9 on kernel32 and user32.

--- B3: 8 MB sliding window (TRIED, NO CHANGE, REVERTED) ---
Changed ZXL_WINDOW from 2 MB to 4 MB (then 8 MB): zero byte change on all 3 files.
Explanation: CHAIN_DEPTH=1024 already caps how far match_find looks, and
for our test files the 1024th-most-recent hash hit is well within 2 MB.
The window size wasn't the bottleneck. Reverted to 2 MB to save ~72 MB RAM.

--- CHAIN_DEPTH 1024 -> 2048 (committed 816a372) ---
Small monotonic gain across all files. Cost: ~2x compression time per position.

--- Intermediate DP match lengths (committed 32ac4b3) ---
Added DP candidate lengths 7, 10, 20, 40, 96, 192 to reduce granularity gaps.
Small monotone improvement without regression.

--- B2: 3-byte MIN_MATCH via TOK_EXACT0 (2026-04-20) ---
New token 0xF4 TOK_EXACT0: 3-byte exact match, 1-byte offset, implicit length 3.
Consumed top of literal-run range; MAX_LIT_RUN dropped 245 -> 244.
New 3-gram hash (short_ht + short_next in MatchCtx); SHORT_DEPTH=64 walk bails
at offset>=256. 6th match candidate (short3) fed to DP with its own overhead
estimate (ovhd_exact0: op + 1*h_off_lo, no length/delta). No REP update on
EXACT0 emission -- disjoint from LRU REP cache to avoid polluting rep[] with
ultra-short local matches.

Context rule tweak: literals are 0x00..0xF3 (not 0xF4); matches are 0xF4..0xFF.
Decoder: 1-byte offset, write 3 bytes directly from ref, do NOT touch rep[].

Results vs pre-B2 baseline (post C1 + CHAIN_DEPTH=2048 + intermediate lengths):
  ntdll.dll:    0.4348 -> 0.4244  (-1.04 pts)
  kernel32.dll: 0.4375 -> 0.4304  (-0.71 pts)
  user32.dll:   0.3579 -> 0.3521  (-0.58 pts)

Now beats bzip2-9 on ALL three files:
  ntdll    ZXL 0.4244 vs bzip2-9 0.4346  (+1.02 pts)
  kernel32 ZXL 0.4304 vs bzip2-9 0.4416  (+1.12 pts)
  user32   ZXL 0.3521 vs bzip2-9 0.3651  (+1.30 pts)

